Hi, I've made the first version of the metronome App with my NES library which is also under development.<br /><br />The only modification to VRAM that I make after each VBlank is update one of three numbers, with a function that reads a 3 character string and outputs it to a Name table using an array that transforms ASCII codes into actual tile numbers.<br />I didn't think that would be so slow to make glitches!<br /><br />What it happens is that when a number is printed, for like one frame the background scrolls so that the 0,0 of the first tile of the string being printed becomes the 0,0 of the screen, I can see this clearly with FCEXUD.<br /><br />Can  you tell me if this problem is that it just takes too long after Vblank or is it something else?<br />Is this unwanted scrolling a normal glitch when violating the VBlank period?<br />Thanks!<br /><br /><a href="http://petruza.com.ar/rnes/NEStronome.nes" class="postlink">http://petruza.com.ar/rnes/NEStronome.nes</a><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3773">Petruza</a> — Tue Jan 20, 2009 5:10 pm</p><hr />
